        "title": "feat(qa): wire Crabline fake provider env",
        "body": "## Summary\n- pass Crabline-provided gateway env into QA Lab spawned runtimes\n- route Slack Web API calls to Crabline via `SLACK_API_URL` / `channels.slack.apiUrl`\n- register a WhatsApp HTTP API active listener when `WHATSAPP_API_ROOT` + `WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN` are present\n- map Crabline WhatsApp manifests to OpenClaw-facing `WHATSAPP_API_ROOT` / `WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN` during QA runs\n- bump QA Lab Crabline dev dependency to `openclaw/crabline@0529a02c992f3ad43bf2a2214e7f4303180e4d06`\n\n## Why\nPR #91502 is already merged. This follow-up makes the merged Crabline fake Slack and WhatsApp provider servers usable from OpenClaw while keeping the WhatsApp plugin interface generic: OpenClaw reads normal provider API env, and QA Lab fills those values from Crabline when the `crabline` channel driver is selected.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/slack/src/client.test.ts extensions/slack/src/config-schema.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/http-api-listener.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/qa-lab/src/qa-transport.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/slack/src/client-options.ts extensions/slack/src/client.ts extensions/slack/src/client.test.ts extensions/slack/src/config-schema.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/provider.ts extensions/slack/src/send.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/heartbeat.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/http-api-listener.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/http-api-listener.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/connection-controller-registry.ts src/config/types.slack.ts src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts`",
